NETWORK SETUP AND CONNECTIVITY TEST REPORT

Title:
Network Setup, Ping Test, and Traceroute Report

Objective:
To set up a basic network, test communication between devices using the ping command, and trace the network path to an internet server using the tracert command.

Network Setup:
1. Connected the Wi-Fi router to the ISP internet connection.
2. Connected the laptop to the Wi-Fi network.
3. Connected a smartphone to the same Wi-Fi network.
4. Verified that both devices received IP addresses automatically using DHCP.
5. Checked the network configuration using the ipconfig command.

Ping Test:
1. Found the smartphone's IP address.
2. Opened Command Prompt on the laptop.
3. Ran the command:
   ping <Smartphone_IP_Address>
4. The ping test was successful while both devices were connected to the same Wi-Fi network.
5. After disconnecting the smartphone from Wi-Fi, the ping command displayed "Request timed out" because the device was no longer reachable.

Traceroute Test:
1. Opened Command Prompt.
2. Ran the command:
   tracert www.youtube.com
3. The output displayed the path (hops) taken by data packets from the laptop to YouTube's server.

Observations:
- Both devices communicated successfully when connected to the same Wi-Fi network.
- The router assigned IP addresses using DHCP.
- Disconnecting the smartphone caused the ping test to fail.
- Traceroute displayed the routers through which the data traveled before reaching the destination.

